"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-news-world-americas-us-politics-trump-paris-olympics-opening-ceremony-b2588140.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  'We will not be having a Last Supper as portrayed the way they portrayed it the other night,' Trump said, referring to the Los Angeles 2028 Olympics  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 447, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 310, \"end\": 315, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999999462061183, \"rank\": 5.3793890215665126e-08, \"text\": \"Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  Donald Trumptouted himself as an \\\"open-minded\\\" individual before ripping into the Paris Olympics opening ceremony for being a \\\"disgrace\\\", following theconservative criticism of an artistic sketch performance at the event.\", \"from\": 448, \"to\": 693, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sitting down with Fox Newsfollowing the 2024 Olympics opening ceremony in Paris on Friday,Trump delivered his own thoughts and opinionson a scene that many had interpreted as being a play on Leonardo Da Vinci's famousThe Last Supperpainting.\", \"from\": 695, \"to\": 936, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 713, \"end\": 716, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_Broadcasting_Company\", \"score\": 0.999831850847035, \"rank\": 0.00015123434097691942, \"text\": \"Fox\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_Broadcasting_Company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_Broadcasting_Company\"}, {\"begin\": 769, \"end\": 774, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999830834, \"rank\": 1.6926892482942866e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 785, \"end\": 790, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999999462061183, \"rank\": 5.3793890215665126e-08, \"text\": \"Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}, {\"begin\": 886, \"end\": 894, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 0.999999999994543, \"rank\": 5.405775654753324e-12, \"text\": \"Leonardo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 895, \"end\": 903, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2164603092173113e-27, \"text\": \"Da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am very open-minded, but I thought what they did was a disgrace,\\\" Trump toldFox News.\", \"from\": 938, \"to\": 1026, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We will not be having aLast Supperas portrayed the way they portrayed it the other night,\\\" he added, referring to the anticipated 2028 Olympics to be held in Los Angeles.\", \"from\": 1028, \"to\": 1199, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1187, \"end\": 1198, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.999999999960437, \"rank\": 3.3805115384078345e-11, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I mean, they can do certain things.\", \"from\": 1201, \"to\": 1237, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I thought it was terrible,\\\" Trump said.\", \"from\": 1238, \"to\": 1277, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1266, \"end\": 1271, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999999462061183, \"rank\": 5.3793890215665126e-08, \"text\": \"Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Look,I am for everybody.\", \"from\": 1278, \"to\": 1303, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am very open-minded... but I thought what they did was a disgrace.\\\"\", \"from\": 1304, \"to\": 1373, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While Christian groups and conservative pundits raised their dismay with the sketch,Paris 2024artistic director Thomas Jolly said the scene had not been inspired byThe Last Supper,and was instead depicting a pagan feast linked to the gods of Olympus in order to celebrate diversity and pay tribute to feasting and French gastronomy.\", \"from\": 1375, \"to\": 1707, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1381, \"end\": 1390, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9951528628070657, \"rank\": 0.004870746216379349, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 1459, \"end\": 1464, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999830834, \"rank\": 1.6926892482942866e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1487, \"end\": 1493, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\", \"score\": 0.9951718775005768, \"rank\": 0.0036749551761462947, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\"}, {\"begin\": 1583, \"end\": 1588, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paganism\", \"score\": 0.999954099300159, \"rank\": 4.581445235956659e-05, \"text\": \"pagan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paganism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paganism\"}, {\"begin\": 1617, \"end\": 1624, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\", \"score\": 0.9950474786431153, \"rank\": 0.004977170504278494, \"text\": \"Olympus\", \"types\": [\"Q8502\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mount_Olympus\"}, {\"begin\": 1689, \"end\": 1695, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.986270120799058, \"rank\": 0.007823375404590124, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The former president is the latest conservative figures to lash out at the performance, with his son Donald Trump Jrreposting a pictureof the performance and stating, \\\"They are not even pretending anymore.\\\"\", \"from\": 1709, \"to\": 1915, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1810, \"end\": 1822, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999999964124981, \"rank\": 2.816042342975924e-09, \"text\": \"Donald Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaker of the House Mike Johnsonalso posted on Xthat the sketch was a \\\"mockery\\\" and was \\\"shocking and insulting to Christian people around the world who watched the opening ceremony of the Olympic Games\\\".\", \"from\": 1917, \"to\": 2122, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1932, \"end\": 1937, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gregory_House\", \"score\": 0.8861979668875123, \"rank\": 0.12831300603729, \"text\": \"House\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gregory_House\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gregory_House\"}, {\"begin\": 2033, \"end\": 2042, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9951528628070657, \"rank\": 0.004870746216379349, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Italy's deputy prime minister Matteo Salvini branded the scene insulting and \\\"sleazy,\\\" adding: \\\"Opening the Olympics by insulting billions of Christians across the world was a really bad start.\\\"\", \"from\": 2124, \"to\": 2318, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2124, \"end\": 2129, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.9992040042360069, \"rank\": 0.0007803806080925674, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}, {\"begin\": 2154, \"end\": 2168, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matteo_Salvini\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matteo Salvini\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matteo_Salvini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matteo_Salvini\"}, {\"begin\": 2266, \"end\": 2276, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.934025587225068, \"rank\": 0.07053386932004731, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Others, such as Elon Musk,called it\\\"extremely disrespectful to Christians,\\\" while Piers Morganalso postedthat it was a \\\"drag queen mockery\\\" and was an \\\"appalling decision\\\".\", \"from\": 2320, \"to\": 2492, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2336, \"end\": 2345, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Elon Musk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elon_Musk\"}, {\"begin\": 2383, \"end\": 2393, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.934025587225068, \"rank\": 0.07053386932004731, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The sketch included drag performers fromDrag Race France,including the show's host, Nicky Doll, who defended the production on her Instagram Stories.\", \"from\": 2494, \"to\": 2643, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2544, \"end\": 2550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9970901524296049, \"rank\": 0.0027911518242900884, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2578, \"end\": 2588, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicky_Doll\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nicky Doll\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicky_Doll\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicky_Doll\"}, {\"begin\": 2625, \"end\": 2642, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Instagram Stories\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was my absolute honor to perform in front of billions of people around the world, and celebrate our Olympians,\\\" Doll wrote on Sunday,themreported.\", \"from\": 2645, \"to\": 2795, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"And remember, to the ones that had their feathers ruffled seeing queerness on their screen: WE AIN'T GOING NOWHERE.\\\"\", \"from\": 2796, \"to\": 2913, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris Olympics officials have apologized to those who took offense at the performance.\", \"from\": 2915, \"to\": 3001, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2915, \"end\": 2929, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We imagined a ceremony to show our values and our principles so we gave a very committed message,\\\" Paris 2024 president Tony Estanguet said.\", \"from\": 3003, \"to\": 3144, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3103, \"end\": 3113, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.7816382489663845e-21, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3124, \"end\": 3138, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tony Estanguet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The idea was to really trigger a reflection.\", \"from\": 3145, \"to\": 3190, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We wanted to have a message as strong as possible.\", \"from\": 3191, \"to\": 3241, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Naturally, we had to take into account the international community.\", \"from\": 3243, \"to\": 3311, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Having said that - it is a French ceremony for the French Games - so we trusted our artistic director.\", \"from\": 3312, \"to\": 3414, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3339, \"end\": 3345, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.986270120799058, \"rank\": 0.007823375404590124, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We have freedom of expression in France and we wanted to protect it.\\\"\", \"from\": 3415, \"to\": 3484, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3448, \"end\": 3454, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9970901524296049, \"rank\": 0.0027911518242900884, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024 spokesperson Anne Descamps told a press conference: \\\"Clearly there was never an intention to show disrespect to any religious group.\", \"from\": 3486, \"to\": 3629, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3486, \"end\": 3496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.7816382489663845e-21, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3515, \"end\": 3523, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Descamps\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(The opening ceremony) tried to celebrate community tolerance.\", \"from\": 3630, \"to\": 3692, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We believe this ambition was achieved.\", \"from\": 3694, \"to\": 3733, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If people have taken any offense, we are really sorry.\\\"\", \"from\": 3734, \"to\": 3789, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jolly also added that the idea of the performance was to spotlight \\\"inclusion\\\" and \\\"diversity.\\\"\", \"from\": 3791, \"to\": 3886, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In France, we have artistic freedom.\", \"from\": 3888, \"to\": 3925, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3892, \"end\": 3898, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9970901524296049, \"rank\": 0.0027911518242900884, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We are lucky in France to live in a free country.\\\"\", \"from\": 3926, \"to\": 3976, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3942, \"end\": 3948, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9970901524296049, \"rank\": 0.0027911518242900884, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies  Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 3978, \"to\": 4208, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4029, \"end\": 4040, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.024370615427111e-22, \"text\": \"Independent\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\"}]}]}"